data.text: I know not whether to rejoice or bemoan this[0a]reunion... Regardless, I must perform my duty.
...This place exists between dream and reality,[0a]mind and matter.
It is a room that only those who are bound by[0a]a contract may enter.
The expression you bear now tells me you[0a]already know the reason for your summons.

I must warn you of the danger threatening to[0a]consume both yourself and the entire world
whose heart you strove so greatly to change.
A most loathsome prison has manifested...[0a]Your appearance is ironclad evidence of this.
You have become a "prisoner of fate" yet again.
That is understandable. This is something only[0a]felt in the depths of one's heart.
Someone, even now, plots to lure you into[0a]a disastrous fate.
Confronted by this evil will, your own cries out:
As one who rules over power, my duty is to[0a]witness the path you take.
Should the world continue down its own[0a]current path, all that awaits you is destruction.

Have you the resolve to defy such a fate and[0a]face the distortion that yet again threatens
your world?
I'm not so sure just yet...
That is the Trickster I know so well.
The time for you to become certain is[0a]drawing nigh.
What awaits you ahead are more of the same—[0a]no, even greater hardships than before.
You must never forget: I am always by your side.
Let us meet again soon. Until then...[0a]pleasant dreams.
